[6] USA (New Jersey, New York)
Date: Tue 13 Nov 2018
Source: Yeshiva World News (YWN World Headquarters - NYC) [abridged, edited]
https://tinyurl.com/yafk2lwn


A measles outbreak is spreading in Charedi [Orthodox Jewish] communities in the Tri-State area [New York metropolitan area], fueled by anti-vaccine propaganda promoted by the anti-vaxxer cult. The outbreak is affecting only members of the Frum community. Not only are the anti-vaxxers responsible for this outbreak, but they are responsible for anti-Semitic propaganda that has begun spreading online -- specifically targeting Jews because of failing to get vaccinated.

- Ocean county, New Jersey (Lakewood): 11 confirmed measles cases, 7 under investigation.
- Brooklyn, New York (Williamsburg, Boro Park, etc.): in the last month, at least 17 cases of measles confirmed in Williamsburg and Borough Park; additional cases under investigation. 2 infants in Intensive Care Unit at Maimonides Medical center.
- Rockland county (Monsey, New Square, Spring Valley): 68 confirmed cases of measles and 11 suspected cases within Rockland county.

